3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22abb6f1da-3ad5-4683-97d4-cf168f45c176%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EBurned%20out%20staffers%20turn%20to%20mental%20health%20leave%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20TikTok%20staffers%20who%20spoke%20with%20BI%20said%20they%20felt%20that%20burnout%20%E2%80%94%20which%20is%20defined%20by%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization%20as%20workplace%20stress%20that%20has%20not%20been%20successfully%20managed%20%E2%80%94%20had%20become%20common.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20employees%20are%20addressing%20burnout%20by%20requesting%20time%20off%20for%20mental%20health%20leave%2C%20five%20of%20the%20current%20and%20former%20employees%20said.%20These%20staffers%20worked%20on%20three%20different%20teams%20across%20several%20offices%20and%20spoke%20directly%20to%20colleagues%20who%20had%20taken%20mental%20health%20leave%20or%20had%20done%20so%20themselves.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%20was%20unable%20to%20obtain%20data%20on%20how%20many%20TikTok%20employees%20have%20used%20mental%20health%20leave%2C%20and%20the%20company%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%20But%20interviews%20with%20current%20and%20former%20staffers%20made%20clear%20that%20mental%20health%20%E2%80%94%20and%20taking%20time%20off%20for%20it%20%E2%80%94%20has%20been%20a%20topic%20of%20discussion%20among%20the%20workforce%20over%20the%20past%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20all%20talked%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20former%20TikTok%20employee%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20all%20side%20texted.%20And%20we%20all%20found%20out%20pretty%20quickly%20whether%20people%20were%20on%20leave%20because%20of%20burnout.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20staffer%20said%20there%20was%20a%20period%20when%20around%2020%25%20of%20their%20team%20was%20out%20on%20mental%20health%20leave.%20While%20TikTok%20doesn't%20broadcast%20why%20a%20worker%20goes%20on%20leave%2C%20the%20staffer%20was%20told%20directly%20by%20colleagues%20that%20they%20were%20taking%20time%20off%20for%20their%20mental%20health.%20A%20second%20current%20staffer%20said%20they%20had%20direct%20knowledge%20of%20six%20employees%20who%20had%20requested%20mental%20health%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20length%20of%20leave%20depended%20on%20the%20individual%20and%20the%20state%20where%20they%20live%2C%20but%20several%20of%20the%20TikTok%20insiders%20said%20two%20to%20three%20months%20of%20paid%20time%20off%20was%20typical.%20When%20a%20staffer%20goes%20on%20leave%2C%20their%20away%20status%20and%20period%20of%20time%20off%20are%20typically%20displayed%20in%20internal%20communication%20tools%20to%20alert%20colleagues%20that%20they%20are%20unreachable%2C%20without%20specifying%20the%20reason%2C%20three%20current%20and%20former%20employees%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20employees%20chose%20to%20go%20on%20leave%20because%20they%20were%20exhausted%20and%20needed%20a%20break%20after%20feeling%20intense%20pressure%20to%20hit%20their%20goals%2C%20said%20three%20of%20the%20TikTok%20insiders%2C%20who%20had%20either%20spoken%20to%20team%20members%20who%20took%20time%20off%20or%20gone%20on%20leave%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20former%20staffer%20described%20a%20moment%20last%20year%20when%20their%20team%20reorganized%20under%20new%20leadership%20and%20saw%20expectations%20around%20performance%20spike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20didn't%20make%20sense%20to%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20have%20ambitious%20goals%2C%20you%20need%20more%20head%20count%2C%20tooling%2C%20and%20software.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20performance%20targets%20increased%2C%20stress%20followed%2C%20a%20third%20former%20staffer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20me%2C%20it%20was%20just%20feeling%20like%20a%20failure%2C%20like%20I%20couldn't%20do%20anything%20right%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20ex-employee%2C%20who%20went%20on%20mental%20health%20leave%20while%20at%20the%20company.%20BI%20viewed%20a%20confirmation%20email%20sent%20to%20the%20employee%20to%20verify%20they%20had%20been%20approved%20for%20the%20leave.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22345007ff-2433-44ae-8b23-d54eb6957337%5C%22%3ETech's%20burnout%20problem%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20isn't%20the%20only%20tech%20company%20dealing%20with%20burnout%2C%20which%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-workers-sick-of-grind-search-low-stress-jobs-burnout-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebecome%20increasingly%20common%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20the%20sector.%20Mental%20health%20leave%20is%20also%20on%20the%20rise%20in%20the%20US%20workforce.%20In%20a%202024%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.littler.com%2Ffiles%2F2024_littler_employer_survey_report.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20US%20business%20executives%20and%20HR%20professionals%20conducted%20by%20the%20law%20firm%20Littler%20Mendelson%2C%2074%25%20of%20respondents%20saw%20an%20increase%20in%20%26quot%3Bemployee%20requests%20for%20leaves%20of%20absence%20or%20accommodations%20for%20mental%20health-related%20issues%20over%20the%20last%20year.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20TikTok%20faces%20unique%20challenges%20when%20compared%20to%20other%20US%20workplaces.%20For%20one%2C%20its%20app%20could%20shut%20down%20in%20the%20US%20in%20April%20if%20it%20fails%20to%20reach%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-us-government-tiktok-stake-could-be-logistical-nightmare-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epolitical%20resolution%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20the%20Trump%20administration.%20While%20TikTok%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-tells-staff-still-have-jobs-if-ban-happens-memo-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eassured%20US%20staffers%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20they%20would%20still%20have%20jobs%20even%20if%20its%20app%20were%20kicked%20out%20of%20the%20country%2C%20the%20company%20rarely%20addresses%20its%20political%20challenges%20internally.%20That's%20added%20to%20overall%20anxiety%2C%20six%20of%20the%20current%20and%20former%20employees%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20uncertainty%20is%20certainly%20playing%20a%20major%20role%20in%20burnout%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20we%20don't%20know%20if%20we're%20going%20to%20have%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20second%20current%20employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22TikTok%20CEO%20Shou%20Zi%20Chew%20testifying%20at%20Capitol%20Hill.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6788a47650dfd88e193eb01d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ETikTok's%20CEO%20Shou%20Chew%20has%20testified%20before%20Congress.%3Cp%3EChip%20Somodevilla%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20for%20some%20staff%2C%20dealing%20with%20challenging%20performance%20standards%20and%20the%20threat%20of%20having%20the%20business%20shut%20down%20by%20the%20US%20government%20is%20worth%20it%20for%20the%20opportunity%20to%20work%20at%20a%20fast-growing%20company%20that%20is%20reshaping%20the%20tech%20industry.%20And%20not%20everyone%20at%20TikTok%20faces%20the%20same%20pressure%20to%20perform%2C%20seven%20of%20the%20current%20and%20former%20staffers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20depending%20on%20the%20team%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20more%20tense%20environment%2C%20but%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20I%20also%20know%20plenty%20of%20teams%20where%20that%20is%20not%20the%20case%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20first%20current%20employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20provides%20various%20mental%20health%20resources%20to%20staff%2C%20including%20therapy%20sessions%2C%20via%20a%20platform%20called%20Lyra%20Health.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2266dd83ce-d252-411e-9811-5dcaccf012b8%5C%22%3E'Building%20the%20plane%20while%20flying%20it'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20and%20its%20parent%20company%2C%20ByteDance%2C%20are%20known%20for%20testing%20many%20ideas%20and%20then%20pivoting%20based%20on%20what%20works%20or%20flops.%20Leaders%20at%20TikTok%20sometimes%20talk%20about%20this%20approach%20as%20%26quot%3Bbuilding%20the%20plane%20while%20flying%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20current%20employee%20and%20two%20former%20staffers%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20that%20startup%20ethos%2C%20the%20company%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaid-off-tiktok-employees-company-reorganization-bytedance-layoffs-social-media-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregularly%20reorganizes%20or%20lays%20off%20teams%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20changes%20employees'%20performance%20goals%2C%20and%20adds%20new%20policies%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-cracks-down-return-to-office-policy-e-commerce-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emandatory%20return-to-office%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20some%20teams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20employees%20said%20that%20frequent%20changes%20to%20how%20they%20worked%2C%20whether%20it%20was%20abruptly%20getting%20a%20new%20manager%20or%20seeing%20their%20goals%20change%2C%20made%20their%20jobs%20feel%20insecure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20joke%20internally%20was%20don't%20get%20too%20comfortable%20because%20something%20was%20going%20to%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20second%20former%20staffer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20reorgs%2C%20some%20new%20team%20leaders%20either%20worked%20out%20of%20China%20(where%20ByteDance%20is%20headquartered)%20and%20required%20late%20calls%20from%20US%20teams%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-ramped-up-hiring-chinese-employees-amid-us-political-scrutiny-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emigrated%20from%20abroad%20to%20work%20in%20US%20offices%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20seven%20of%20the%20current%20and%20former%20staffers%20told%20BI.%20Managers%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faffiliate.insider.com%3Fh%3De387879e9c07fe1018cc1fd5dc29d5c056a9819bab6090a07846572