Tok%20said%20that%20its%20US%20platform%20is%20controlled%20by%20US%20employees%2C%20subsidiaries%2C%20and%20contractors%2C%20but%20that%20its%20recommendation%20algorithm%20is%20developed%20by%20a%20global%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20former%20employees%2C%20such%20as%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-tiktok-employees-describe-996-culture-overtime-and-secrecy-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChloe%20Shih%20and%20Pabel%20Martinez%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20previously%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20intensity%20of%20the%20company's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-employees-say-staff-in-china-make-many-product-decisions-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20focus%20on%20working%20long%20hours%20isn't%20new%20to%20the%20China%20tech%20scene.%20Tech%20firms%20like%20ByteDance%20built%20massive%20businesses%20in%20the%20country%20as%20part%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F996-work-culture-schedule-popular-in-china-explained-2021-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3B996%26quot%3B%20work%20culture%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20asked%20employees%20to%20work%209%20a.m.%20to%209%20p.m.%2C%20six%20days%20a%20week%20(a%20practice%20that%20is%20now%20illegal%20in%20China).%20Even%20as%20ByteDance%20has%20pledged%20to%20work%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2021%2F11%2F01%2Fchina-tiktok-bytedance-workers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3B1075%26quot%3B%20schedule%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%2010%20a.m.%20to%207%20p.m.%2C%20five%20days%20a%20week%20%E2%80%94%20there%20remains%20a%20sense%20among%20some%20US%20employees%20that%20their%20Chinese%20colleagues%20are%20constantly%20working.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20were%20a%20lot%20of%20leaders%20that%20came%20in%20from%20ByteDance%20or%20the%20China-based%20teams%2C%20and%20they%20operated%20so%20differently%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20fourth%20former%20employee%20said.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20cultural%20perspective%20that%20the%20US%20and%20outside%20of%20China%20just%20doesn't%20work%20as%20fast%20as%20China.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22ByteDance%20founder%20Zhang%20Yiming%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67cf1d8c69253ccddf98c608%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222560%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EByteDance%20founder%20Zhang%20Yiming%20is%20one%20of%20the%20wealthiest%20individuals%20in%20China%2C%20per%20Forbes%20and%20Bloomberg%20estimates.%3Cp%3EVCG%2FVCG%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pressure%20to%20always%20be%20available%20can%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20burnout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20not%20machines%2C%20and%20giving%20them%20breaks%20to%20recharge%2C%20to%20think%20differently%2C%20helps%20our%20employees%20be%20more%20creative%2C%26quot%3B%20Jaclyn%20Margolis%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20who%20researches%20organizational%20behavior%20at%20Pepperdine%20University's%20Graziadio%20Business%20School%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFailure%20to%20address%20burnout%20can%20lead%20to%20absenteeism%20and%20turnover%2C%20said%20Laura%20Giurge%2C%20an%20assistant%20professor%20at%20the%20London%20School%20of%20Economics%20and%20Political%20Science.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20economic%20impact%20of%20burnout%20in%20the%20workplace%20can%20be%20sizable.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ajpmonline.org%2Farticle%2FS0749-3797(25)00023-6%2Fabstract%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2025%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20American%20Journal%20of%20Preventive%20Medicine%20estimated%20that%20employee%20disengagement%20and%20burnout%20cost%20US%20companies%20between%20%243%2C999%20and%20%2420%2C683%20a%20year%20per%20disengaged%20staffer%2C%20depending%20on%20the%20level%20of%20seniority.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ccf463fb-7153-4196-8420-253a47ae5af7%5C%22%3ETikTok's%20'golden%20handcuffs'%20and%20a%20tough%20job%20market%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20working%20at%20TikTok%20can%20be%20grueling%20for%20some%20US%20employees%2C%20the%20company%20also%20pays%20its%20staff%20competitively%20%E2%80%94%20a%20key%20perk.%20A%20BI%20analysis%20of%20work-visa%20disclosures%20from%20late%202024%20found%20that%20with%20a%20few%20exceptions%2C%20most%20of%20the%20company's%20base%20salary%20offers%20were%20in%20the%20six%20figures%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFear%20of%20losing%20a%20high%20salary%20acts%20as%20a%20form%20of%20%26quot%3Bgolden%20handcuffs%26quot%3B%20for%20TikTok%20employees%2C%20the%20third%20former%20staffer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20also%20no%20guarantee%20that%20leaving%20TikTok%20for%20a%20competitor%20would%20reduce%20workplace%20stress%2C%20as%20other%20Big%20Tech%20firms%20have%20also%20increased%20pressure%20on%20staff%20as%20part%20of%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-firms-laying-off-employees-again-efficiency-amazon-google-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eongoing%20efficiency%20push%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20an%20employee%20wants%20to%20jump%20ship%2C%20it%20may%20be%20tough%20to%20land%20a%20new%20gig%2C%20as%20the%20tech%20job%20market%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjobs-software-engineers-coders-bad-market-ai-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Every%20tight%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20of%20February%2C%20US%20software%20development%20job%20postings%20were%20around%2036.5%25%20below%20their%20pre-pandemic%20levels%2C%20according%20to%20data%20compiled%20by%20the%20jobs%20site%20Indeed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAllison%20Shrivastava%2C%20an%20economist%20with%20the%20Indeed%20Hiring%20Lab%2C%20said%20there's%20uncertainty%20in%20the%20job%20market%20and%20quit%20rates%20are%20very%20low.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20tech%20scene%20elsewhere%20has%20been%20really%20rough%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20third%20current%20employee%20said.%20%26quot%3BFeeling%20kind%20of%20stuck.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20for%20the%20thousands%20of%20employees%20working%20in%20TikTok's%20US%20offices%2C%20the%20issue%20of%20job%20security%20is%20particularly%20heightened%20as%20we%20approach%20April%205%2C%20the%20deadline%20for%20TikTok%20to%20make%20a%20deal%20that%20appeases%20Washington.%20A%20divest-or-ban%20law%2C%20which%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20upheld%20as%20constitutional%2C%20has%20targeted%20ByteDance's%20ties%20to%20China.%20Without%20additional%20government%20intervention%2C%20TikTok%20could%20disappear%20from%20app%20stores%20and%20potentially%20cease%20operating%20in%20less%20than%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20people%20wonder%20why%20we%20are%20doing%20this%20job%2C%20because%20in%20a%20few%20weeks%2C%20it%20may%20no%20longer%20be%20relevant%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20first%20current%20staffer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20email%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Adwhateley%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Edwhateley%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20or%20Signal%20at%20%40danwhateley.94.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%20and%20a%20nonwork%20device%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere's%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAshley%20Rodriguez%20contributed%20reporting.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-staff-burn-out-workplace-performance-pressure-mental-health-leave-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusi