businessinsider.com%2Ftexas-stargate-data-center-build-cost-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStargate%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January%2C%20he%20said%20the%20massive%20AI%20infrastructure%20project%E2%80%94a%20joint%20venture%20formed%20by%20OpenAI%2C%20Oracle%2C%20and%20SoftBank%E2%80%94would%20create%20%26quot%3Bover%20100%2C000%20American%20jobs%20almost%20immediately.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELittle%20evidence%20supports%20the%20accuracy%20of%20Trump's%20statement%2C%20though%20he%20wouldn't%20be%20the%20first%20politician%20to%20suggest%20that%20data%20centers%20are%20a%20boon%20for%20job%20creation.%20The%20data%20center%20industry%20has%20grown%20rapidly%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20and%20state%20governors%20have%20touted%20the%20jobs%20it%20would%20create.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20study%20from%20PwC%20supports%20these%20claims%2C%20reporting%20that%20data%20centers%20contributed%204.7%20million%20jobs%20to%20national%20employment%20in%202023%2C%20up%2060%25%20from%202017.%20While%20the%20data%20center%20market%20has%20grown%20rapidly%20in%20recent%20years%20and%20has%20been%20fueled%20by%20the%20rise%20of%20cloud%20computing%20and%20AI%2C%20most%20of%20those%20jobs%20aren't%20direct%20tech%20jobs.%20Economic%20development%20experts%20are%20divided%20over%20the%20accuracy%20of%20the%20study%2C%20which%20was%20sponsored%20by%20data%20center%20industry%20lobbying%20group%20Data%20Center%20Coalition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBig%20Tech%20companies%20spent%20a%20combined%20estimated%20%24246%20billion%20in%20capital%20expenditures%20last%20year%2C%20much%20of%20which%20was%20on%20data%20center%20expansion.%20Amazon%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20Meta%20are%20expected%20to%20spend%20another%20%24320%20billion%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-tech-ai-capex-spend-meta-google-amazon-microsoft-earnings-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20capital%20expenditures%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EState%20and%20local%20government%20officials%20have%20touted%20the%20number%20of%20jobs%20that%20would%20result%20from%20all%20the%20new%20development.%20However%2C%20once%20built%2C%20data%20center%20facilities%20don't%20employ%20large%20numbers%20of%20permanent%20employees%2C%20and%20the%20economic%20development%20contracts%20they%20sign%20in%20exchange%20for%20tax%20incentives%20often%20reflect%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20press%20release%20announcing%20Amazon's%20%2410%20billion%20data%20center%20expansion%20in%20Ohio%2C%20Gov.%20Mike%20DeWine%20said%20in%20December%20that%20the%20investment%20would%20support%20%26quot%3Bthousands%26quot%3B%20of%20jobs.%20Documents%20filed%20with%20the%20Ohio%20Department%20of%20Development%20showed%20that%20Amazon%20is%20committed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-invests-10-billion-ohio-data-centers-energy-concerns-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecreating%201%2C058%20new%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20none%20of%20which%20are%20required%20to%20be%20full-time%2C%20salaried%20positions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e749ad3e-e32a-407d-a377-f7521e7a894d%5C%22%3EThe%20data%20center%20industry%20overhypes%20job%20creation%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%204.7%20million%20jobs%20attributed%20to%20the%20data%20center%20industry%20in%20the%20PwC%20study%2C%20only%20603%2C900%20were%20actual%20industry%20jobs%2C%20otherwise%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bdirect%26quot%3B%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Data%20Center%20Coalition%2C%20an%20industry%20lobbying%20group%20that%20counts%20Amazon%2C%20Microsoft%2C%20Google%2C%20and%20Meta%20as%20members%2C%20commissioned%20the%20PwC%20study%2C%20which%20grouped%20jobs%20into%20three%20categories%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bdirect%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bindirect%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Binduced.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%26quot%3Bdirect%26quot%3B%20job%2C%20the%20study%20said%2C%20is%20any%20job%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0full-time%2C%20part-time%2C%20or%20self-employed%20%E2%80%94%20tied%20to%20the%20operation%20of%20the%20data%20center.%20An%20%26quot%3Bindirect%26quot%3B%20job%20refers%20to%20a%20full-time%2C%20part-time%2C%20or%20self-employed%20job%20created%20to%20produce%20necessary%20goods%20and%20services%20in%20a%20data%20center's%20supply%20chain.%20%26quot%3BInduced%26quot%3B%20jobs%20are%20jobs%20that%20result%20from%20spending%20that%20occurs%20in%20an%20area%20due%20to%20the%20data%20center's%20presence%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENearly%204.1%20million%20data%20center%20jobs%20%E2%80%94%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20total%20number%20of%20data%20center%20jobs%20accounted%20for%20in%20PwC's%20study%20%E2%80%94%20were%20considered%20indirect%20and%20induced.%20Indirect%20and%20induced%20jobs%20can%20comprise%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20potential%20positions%2C%20from%20the%20construction%20and%20maintenance%20of%20data%20centers%20to%20jobs%20in%20the%20local%20service%20industry%20near%20the%20data%20centers.%20The%20service%20sector%2C%20which%20includes%20everything%20from%20tourism%2C%20hospitality%2C%20and%20retail%2C%20to%20healthcare%20and%20financial%20services%2C%20accounted%20for%2060%25%20of%20the%20data%20center%20industry's%20induced%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDCC%20asked%20PwC%20to%20quantify%20the%20economic%20contributions%20made%20by%20the%20data%20center%20industry%20nationally%20as%20well%20as%20in%20each%20state%20and%20the%20District%20of%20Columbia.%20The%20report%20and%20analysis%20were%20conducted%20independently%20by%20PwC%20using%20publicly%20available%20government%20data%20from%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Economic%20Analysis%20and%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20Data%20Center%20Coalition%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20economists%20say%20induced%20and%20indirect%20jobs%20can%20be%20difficult%20to%20accurately%20quantify.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENathan%20Jensen%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Texas's%20Department%20of%20Government%2C%20questioned%20the%20study's%20estimate%20of%20the%20number%20of%20jobs%20created%20by%20the%20data%20center%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20economic%20impact%20of%20these%20projects%20aren't%20particularly%20high%2C%26quot%3B%20Jensen%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20head-shaking%20to%20me%20how%20you%20could%20come%20up%20with%20that%20jobs%20number.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPwC%20used%20IMPLAN%2C%20an%20economic%20modeling%20software%20that%20is%20considered%20an%20industry%20standard%20for%20economic%20impact%20analysis%20and%20data.%20While%20IMPLAN%20has%20been%20used%20since%20the%20late%201970s%20to%20demonstrate%20potential%20job%20creation%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20industries%2C%20Jensen%20said%20the%20program%20is%20vulnerable%20to%20misuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20controversy%20around%20IMPLAN%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20often%20used%20to%20justify%20economic%20development%20incentives.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIMPLAN's%20model%20relies%20on%20the%20North%20American%20Industry%20Classification%20System%2C%20which%20the%20federal%20government%20uses%20to%20classify%20businesses%2C%20to%20determine%20the%20%26quot%3Bmultiplier%20effect%26quot%3B%20of%20an%20economic%20development%20project%20to%20measure%20the%20overall%20impact%20on%20the%20local%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPwC%20determined%20that%20the%20data%20center%20industry%20has%20a%20multiplier%20effect%20of%207.5%2C%20meaning%20that%20every%20direct%20data%20center%20job%20leads%20to%20another%207.5%20jobs%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20US%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJensen%20said%20a%20multiplier%20effect%20of%20one%20or%20two%20is%20likely%20more%20accurate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22889bbd4b-d728-48e9-8935-385e74c05a9e%5C%22%3EThe%20data%20center%20boom%20creates%20construction%20jobs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EData%20centers%20do%20offer%20significant%20job%20creation%20opportunities%2C%20said%20John%20Boyd%20Jr.%2C%20principal%20at%20site%20selection%20advisory%20The%20Boyd%20Co.%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0it's%20just%20that%20the%20jobs%20are%20in%20unexpected%20places.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConstruction%20jobs%20are%20bigger%20and%20more%20important%20to%20the%20data%20center%20industry%20than%20people%20realize%2C%20he%20said.%20Boyd's%20firm%20has%20helped%20large%20corporations%20like%20AT%26amp%3BT%2C%20Dell%2C%20and%20Visa%20choose%20locations%20for%20major%20development%20projects%2C%20and%20it%20has%20also%20advised%20government%20agencies%20on%20economic%20development%20deals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20actual%20amount%20of%20on-site%20labor%20is%20enormous%2C%20and%20wages%20are%20over%20double%20the%20national%20average%20for%20construction%20workers%2C%26quot%3B%20Boyd%20said%20of%20data%20center%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20because%20data%20center%20construction%20requires%20skilled%20labor%20across%20a%20variety%20of%20expertise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20looking%20at%20cooling%20systems%2C%20natural%20gas%20turbines%2C%20specialized%20server%20equipment%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConstruction%20workers%20often%20travel%20to%20data%20center%20sites%20and%20stay%20for%20extended%20periods%20of%20time%2C%20which%20leads%20to%20a%20need%20for%20hotels%2C%20restaurants%2C%20and%20other%20services.%20The%20data%20center%20development%20boom%20has%20led%20to%20a%20surge%20in%20occupancy%20rates%20at%20properties%20owned%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwyndham-q4-2024-earnings-data-centers-boost-growth-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWyndham%20Hotels%20and%20Resorts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20CEO%20Geoff%20Ballotti%20said%20on%20the%20company%20earnings%20call%20in%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20centers%20also%20require%20routine%20and%20specialized%20maintenance%20after%20they%20are%20built%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20continued%20need%20for%20skilled%20labor%20nearby.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20industry%20tends%20to%20cluster%20to