Etoxic%20workplace%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20a%20third%20of%20that%20group%20said%20their%20boss%20is%20to%20blame.%20Recently%2C%20frustrated%20workers%20have%20been%20calling%20out%20their%20managers%20for%20bad%20behavior%2C%20taking%20to%20LinkedIn%20to%20air%20grievances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-vp-of-hr-microsoft-traits-bad-manager-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBad%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Breally%20have%20a%20negative%20trickle%20effect%20down%20to%20all%20the%20employees%20on%20the%20team%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Sharon%20Grossman%2C%20a%20counselor%20and%20executive%20coach%20specializing%20in%20workplace%20stress%20reduction%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Over%20time%2C%20working%20for%20one%20can%20impact%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftoxic-boss-ruined-confidence-gaslighting-self-doubt-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eself-confidence%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20motivation%20at%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToxic%20bosses%20come%20in%20all%20forms.%20They%20can%20micromanage%20you%20or%20expect%20you%20to%20work%20weekends.%20They%20can%20be%20disorganized%20or%20conflict-avoidant%2C%20causing%20team-wide%20issues.%20At%20their%20worst%2C%20they%20can%20be%20aggressive%20or%20fail%20to%20give%20your%20work%20due%20credit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20thing%20they%20all%20have%20in%20common%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20lack%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-leaders-can-build-emotional-intelligence-2021-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eemotional%20intelligence%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20Dr.%20Zachary%20Ginder%2C%20a%20psychologist%20specializing%20in%20occupational%20stress%20reduction%2C%20told%20BI.%20He%20said%20their%20shortcomings%20can%20be%20heightened%20if%20they%20clash%20with%20their%20employee's%20work%20style%20%E2%80%94%20for%20example%2C%20a%20scattered%20boss%20with%20a%20hyper-organized%20direct%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20workarounds.%20Ginder%20and%20Grossman%20shared%20tips%20on%20how%20to%20navigate%20working%20with%20each%20type%20of%20bad%20boss%20%E2%80%94%20and%20how%20to%20know%20when%20to%20leave%20for%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222d5c3040-346f-41ff-b890-13084be7a5aa%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20micromanager%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicromanager-boss-being-better-manager-tips-advice-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicromanagers%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Boften%20operate%20from%20a%20place%20of%20distrust%20and%20a%20sense%20of%20low-grade%20anxiety%2C%26quot%3B%20Ginder%20said.%20Your%20best%20bet%20is%20to%20make%20sure%20they%20know%20you're%20on%20top%20of%20your%20work%2C%20even%20if%20you%20have%20to%20overcommunicate%20at%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20your%20micromanager%20likes%20to%20schedule%20check-ins%2C%20you%20can%20meet%20them%20halfway%20by%20suggesting%20a%20time%20first.%20For%20example%2C%20you%20can%20say%20%26quot%3BLet's%20chat%20about%20this%20in%20two%20days%2C%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20that%20way%2C%20they%20know%20you'll%20finish%20on%20time%20%26quot%3Bwithout%20them%20having%20to%20hover%2C%26quot%3B%20Grossman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGinder%20said%20you%20can%20also%20share%20progress%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ebefore%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0they%20request%20it%2C%20setting%20personal%20reminders%20to%20send%20them%20regular%20updates%20and%20using%20project%20management%20tools%20to%20your%20advantage%20by%20being%20transparent%20about%20what%20you're%20working%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227bfe6d47-5356-4122-b9fa-667d591738f2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20ghost%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20shadow%20side%20of%20a%20micromanager%20is%20one%20who%20barely%20manages%20at%20all.%20They%20might%20never%20check%20in%20or%20be%20inconsistent%20with%20getting%20back%20to%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGinder%20said%20these%20managers%20might%20be%20indecisive%2C%20conflict-avoidant%2C%20or%20just%20lacking%20in%20time-management%20skills.%20Either%20way%2C%20you'll%20need%20to%20find%20a%20way%20to%20reduce%20the%20bottlenecks%20in%20your%20workflow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou'll%20have%20to%20%26quot%3Bpin%20them%20down%26quot%3B%20as%20best%20you%20can%2C%20Grossman%20said.%20If%20they%20haven't%20established%20a%20check-in%20time%2C%20set%20one%20up%20first.%20Ginder%20recommended%20making%20day-to-day%20communication%20as%20clear%20as%20possible%2C%20such%20as%20breaking%20down%20to-dos%20into%20smaller%20tasks%20or%20writing%20out%20the%20pros%20and%20cons%20of%20big%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20they're%20flaky%20even%20then%2C%20Ginder%20recommends%20finding%20ways%20to%20do%20your%20job%20without%20your%20boss's%20sign-off.%20If%20you%20can%20reach%20out%20to%20other%20members%20of%20your%20team%20with%20decision-making%20authority%2C%20that%20collaboration%20can%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20work%20around%20your%20boss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226db63fc6-95c5-430e-9813-5bd1721bdb17%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20boundary-less%20boss%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20manager%20who%20works%20overtime%20and%20weekends%20might%20expect%20you%20to%20do%20the%20same%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bjust%20because%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftoxic-boss-used-me-everything-did-all-jobs-quit-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboss%20has%20no%20boundaries%3C%2Fa%3E%20doesn't%20mean%20that%20you%20can't%20have%20boundaries%2C%26quot%3B%20Grossman%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20ahead%20of%20the%20issue%2C%20Ginder%20said%20you%20can%20softly%20set%20the%20timeline%20first.%20%26quot%3BI%20see%20this%20rolling%20out%20over%20the%20next%20several%20weeks%26quot%3B%20creates%20more%20of%20an%20opportunity%20to%20negotiate%20a%20deadline%2C%20rather%20than%20having%20to%20finish%20ASAP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20that%20doesn't%20work%2C%20you%20have%20to%20be