rably%20harmed%20by%20an%20indefinite%20delay%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20FOIA%20requests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20DOGE%20to%20deliver%20the%20requested%20information%20quickly%20and%20%26quot%3Bbegin%20producing%20documents%20on%20a%20rolling%20basis%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECooper's%20decision%20is%20the%20first%20major%20legal%20ruling%20that%20has%20sought%20to%20pry%20open%20DOGE's%20operations%20for%20the%20public.%20His%20memo%20mainly%20cited%20news%20reports%20and%20social%20media%20statements%20from%20Musk%20and%20President%20Donald%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20the%20ruling%20can%20be%20appealed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20note%2C%20Cooper%20wrote%20that%20DOGE's%20actions%20%26quot%3Bdemonstrate%20its%20substantial%20authority%20over%20vast%20swaths%20of%20the%20federal%20government.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20wrote%20that%20DOGE%20appeared%20to%20have%20access%20to%20much%20of%20the%20government's%20IT%20systems%2C%20allowing%20it%20to%20act%20and%20move%20quickly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20the%20rapid%20pace%20of%20USDS's%20actions%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20requires%20the%20quick%20release%20of%20information%20about%20its%20structure%20and%20activities%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added%2C%20citing%20the%20agency%20as%20the%20US%20DOGE%20Service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20Trump%20took%20office%20in%20January%2C%20DOGE's%20mandate%20has%20been%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-department-of-government-efficiency%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eax%20government%20spending%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20name%20of%20efficiency.%20As%20part%20of%20that%20effort%2C%20it's%20canceled%20most%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarco-rubio-announces-official-end-of-most-usaid-programs-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUSAID%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnasa-reduction-in-force-plans-department-closures-doge-firings-trump-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efired%20thousands%20of%20federal%20employees.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EData%20released%20this%20month%20by%20Challenger%2C%20Gray%20%26amp%3B%20Christmas%20showed%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-job-cuts-layoffs-highest-level-2020-covid-pandemic-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejob%20cuts%20in%20the%20federal%20government%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20reached%20172%2C017%20in%20February%20alone%20%E2%80%94%20the%20highest%20monthly%20level%20since%20the%20pandemic%20spurred%20a%20wave%20of%20layoffs%20in%20June%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDOGE%20estimates%20it's%20saved%20%24105%20billion%20so%20far%2C%20but%20its%20tallies%20aren't%20definitive.%20The%20agency%20has%20repeatedly%20deleted%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-elon-musk-delete-4-billion-savings-wall-of-receipts-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elowered%20the%20amount%20saved%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20some%20of%20its%20reports%20by%20billions%20of%20dollars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20memo%2C%20Cooper%20cited%20multiple%20concerns%20with%20how%20DOGE%20was%20working%2C%20writing%20that%20it%20operates%20with%20%26quot%3Bunusual%20secrecy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECooper%20referred%20to%20several%20news%20reports%2C%20such%20as%20a%20piece%20from%20The%20New%20York%20Times%20that%20found%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdoge-second-productivity-email-federal-workers-more-soon-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDOGE%20employees%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20operating%20on%20auto-deleting%20messaging%20apps%20like%20Signal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMoreover%2C%20the%20authority%20exercised%20by%20USDS%20across%20the%20federal%20government%20and%20the%20dramatic%20cuts%20it%20has%20apparently%20made%20with%20no%20congressional%20input%20appear%20to%20be%20unprecedented%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20line%20with%20C